gomodel:SYNGO_4986  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Figure 3: Defective presynaptic maturation and function in Lnx1-null mice. EM imaging of mossy-fiber synapses in wildtype and Lnx1 -/- mice showed deficits in PSD number per spine, docked synaptic vesicles per release site and synaptic vesicle density.\n\nFigure 4: Reverse IPs with knockout and mutated-domain controls showed Lnx1 and EphB1/2 can interact.\n\nFigure 5: Lnx1 stabilizes EphB receptors through specific binding sites to prevent their degradation in proteasome.\n\nFigure 8: The diminished axon terminals in Lnx1-/- mice (Figure 3, 8a) were restored in mice with both Lnx1-/- and EphB2F620D/F620D mutations. The latter is a constitutively active form of EphB tyrosine kinase.\n\nTaken together, authors showed that Lnx1 mediated EphB1 and EphB2 kinase activation promotes mossy fiber presynaptic terminal maturation (Figure 8H).. Experimental description: From results, Figure 3 legend: \"Defective presynaptic maturation and function in Lnx1-null mice\"\n\nLnx1 mutatant mice were generated by authors, as detailed in M&M section \"Generation of Lnx1 mutant mice\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2023-02-08" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4986" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

